Acme questions
1)in your opinion, is an important part of code reviews? That is, what is
  something you pay attention to when you review code, and that you appreciate
  when others do the same for your code?

Code reviews have several parts that are in important. 
First this helps you mininmize the amount of mistakes you make when you are writing code. 
A partner reviewing your code can help debug and find errors you didn't know existed.
Another thing is that, code reviews helps make sure you fulfill your target/goal. 
Reviewing with another person can help make sure all requirements for the task was met.
Your confidence level can also rise during a code review. It'll help better understand
the work you completed and also brings positive status towards the future when coding. 

2) We have an awful lot of computers here, and it gets pretty confusing with
  slightly different things running on all of them. How could containers help us
  improve this situation?


Well to start with, containers are an operatin system virtualiztion. One contianer can be used
to run anything from small to large apps. Containers contain codes, libraries, and even foles. 
Benefits of containers weoulf be they require a lot less system resources. Apps running in containers 
can be deployed easily to multiple different operating systems. 